      "writtenOn": "2016-01-09T01:27:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "if any thread is killed in a middle of its operation, the whole app state is completely screwed. We shouldn\u0027t even care about such cases (and should never do anything like that)\n\nE.g. if the thread was in a middle of new() call, which locked the memory manager\u0027s mutex, and it was shot dead, mutex would remain locked for the whole app forever. Any other library call might do the same thing.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 89,
        "endChar": 37
      },
